-- Canada’s Harper Says He Expects 2013 Jobs to Be Positive
-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 2013-02-08T18:36:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-08/canada-s-harper-says-he-expects-2013-jobs-trend-to-be-positive.html
Canadian Prime Minister Stephen
Harper said that while he’s disappointed about job losses in
January the trend in recent months has been positive.  Speaking to reporters near Vancouver, Harper said he’s
optimistic the “pattern” for jobs will continue to be positive
in 2013.  Statistics Canada reported today employment fell by 21,900
in January, the first decline in six months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theophilos Argitis in Ottawa at 
 targitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
